(1) There shall be a Surveyor-General who shall be a public officer and land surveyor .
There shall be a Surveyor-General who shall be a public officer and land surveyor .
(2) Subject to the general or special directions of the Minister, the Surveyor-General shall— (a) supervise and control the survey and charting of land for the purposes of registration ; (b) take charge of and preserve all records appertaining to the survey of parcels of land which have been approved; (c) direct and supervise the conduct of such trigonometrical, topographical and level surveys, and such geodetic and geophysical operations, as the Minister may direct; (d) take charge of and preserve the records of all surveys and operations carried out under paragraph (c); (e) supervise the preparation of such maps as the Minister may direct from the data derived from any surveys, and the amendment of such maps; and (f) generally administer the provisions of this Act.
