When submitting to the Surveyor-General for approval the records of a subdivisional survey , the land surveyor concerned shall deliver, in addition to any other records—
(a) a plan showing the proposed subdivision or subdivisions approved by the appropriate authority constituted under the Town and Country Planning Act when the land is subject to the provisions of that Act;
a plan showing the proposed subdivision or subdivisions approved by the appropriate authority constituted under the Town and Country Planning Act when the land is subject to the provisions of that Act;
(b) in the case of land leased from the President, a plan of the proposed subdivision or subdivisions approved by the Commissioner of Lands.
